---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { site } from '../lib/site';
import { href } from '../lib/url';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclosure"
  description="How Floor Life makes money, how affiliate links work, and the plain fact that nothing here is medical advice."
>
  <PageHeader eyebrow="Plain and up front" title="Disclosure" />

  <div class="prose prose-floor mx-auto mt-12 max-w-2xl px-5 pb-8 sm:px-8">
    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Some outbound links to products are <strong>affiliate links</strong>. If you
      click one and buy something, {site.name} may earn a small commission — at no
      additional cost to you. Those links are marked technically with
      <code>rel="sponsored nofollow"</code>, and near any group of them you'll find
      a short note saying so.
    </p>
    <p>
      Commissions never change what we recommend or what we say about it. We list
      things because we think they're good, and we tell you where they fall short.
      When something is expensive, direct-sale, or has no affiliate program at all
      (the Soul Seat, for one), we still link it if it's the right answer — we'd
      rather be useful than paid.
    </p>

    <h2>Prices</h2>
    <p>
      Prices move constantly, especially on marketplaces. Every figure here is a
      rough, mid-2026 estimate — always check the live price at the link before
      buying.
    </p>

    <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
    <p>
      Floor Life is an editorial project about movement and home design, not a
      medical service. Nothing here is medical, physical-therapy, or diagnostic
      advice. Floor sitting and deep positions carry real, if modest, risks —
      especially for people with knee or hip osteoarthritis, after a joint
      replacement, during pregnancy, or with balance concerns.
    </p>
    <p>
      Build up gradually, stay within a pain-free range, vary your positions, and
      talk to a qualified professional before making changes if you have any
      doubt. You are responsible for your own body.
    </p>

    <h2>Honesty</h2>
    <p>
      We try hard to separate what the evidence supports from what merely sounds
      good, and to cite sources on the <a href={href('/why')}>why</a> page. If
      we get something wrong, we'd genuinely like to know.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
